<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-1')">1</a>. This is SWN001-1-CH00 (better known as <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ch00bakka" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1238719); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1238719&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437323" alt="ch00bakka" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1238719)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ch00bakka" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1238719); return false;">ch00bakka</a></span>) speaking. I'm pretty sure that characters can't see footnotes, so this is where you're gonna get all the sweet, sweet author commentary. (In case there's any confusion, I am not S Andrew Swann and I didn't write that 001 proposal—I just think it's neat.)</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-2')">2</a>. Love me some ancient gays &lt;3. There was a legit ancient rumor that Hadrian killed his boyfriend to cure him of some illness and this is an SCP for that. I think the MCD report isn't as good as it could be. I do like the poem I wrote in the SCP article and I think I should've written it in Latin also because poetic composition in dead languages usually impresses people. Also the name is a pun on Hadrian's Wall because, well, duh.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-3"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-3')">3</a>. The inspiration for this one was that I visited the upper end of the Aqua Claudia while I was studying abroad in Rome. It was the first appearance of the CPSO, which actually has enough articles to get a tag but I might wait a little while to see if rules for tag proposals change.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-4"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-4')">4</a>. Hnnnnnnghhhhh i want this to have more votes I don't know if I just posted it at a bad time and nobody saw it or if it's too long and nobody's finished it. Anyway I think it's good. It's literally just that the title &quot;Emperor of Rome&quot; is anomalous because Augustus fuckin sacrificed himself. That's pretty metal.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-5"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-5')">5</a>. My entry for JamCon2019 Day One: Shaggy Dog. It's got a terrible pun at the end.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-6"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-6')">6</a>. The chaos insurgency is boring as hell most of the time. I'm here to fix that. i have no idea where this idea came from, i just fuckin sat down at work and wrote it. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">this miiiiiight be the start of a series? i'm not sure. if so i'll definitely do a little more explaining,</span> but this first tale is mostly just self-contained weirdness and an introduction to the character. Ok it is the start of a series and i'm linking the hub instead. title comes from Channel Z by the B52s; it was gonna be &quot;Head Like a Hole&quot; but someone beat me to the punch on that by like two weeks.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-7"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-7')">7</a>. ever since Randomini introduced her, we've seen Iris Dark a lot. I decided to focus on the Old Dark. inspired by a conversation <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3938622&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437323" alt="The Great Hippo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3938622)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;">The Great Hippo</a></span> was having with <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gabriel-jade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(414239); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=414239&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437323" alt="Gabriel Jade" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=414239)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gabriel-jade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(414239); return false;">Gabriel Jade</a></span> on irc that ended up going in a different direction to this concept but i would feel weird not crediting the inspiration. title is from Party Out of Bounds by the B52s.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-8"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-8')">8</a>. SCP-2517 - This One Time I Saw God On Shrooms
<p>Subtitled &quot;God Was On Shrooms, Not Me&quot;.</p>
<p>This one was inspired by a really intense mushroom trip during which I saw the fnords on my ceiling. It's heavily based on qntm's <a href="/antimemetics-division-hub">Antimemetics Division</a> stuff, but it shouldn't require prior knowledge of that canon. It’s a hallucinogenic mushroom that acts as a mnestic and also cushions your mind from harmful memetic effects; it lets you see the Fifth Church's God/<a href="/scp-3125">SCP-3125</a>, an extradimensional meme-based organism that kills you and everyone with a similar mind if you perceive it. The mushrooms protect you from being erased and stop it from noticing you if you don't use them regularly, but don't protect your friends and family.</p>
<p>&quot;Megatyphro&quot; means &quot;Big Cheese&quot; in Greek, so Saint-Archon Horatius Megatyphro is Celebration &quot;Big Cheese&quot; Horace.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-9"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-9')">9</a>. A tale about my alma mater, based on a running joke my friends had in college. My first tale ever, although it's not really a tale in the narrative sense; but there's nothing between tale and GoI format to categorize it as.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-10"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-10')">10</a>. I wrote this one in 2011, when I was 15 years old. I'm gonna be bitter forever until it's not my highest-rated article. I just don't think it's very good. It used to like&#8230;.. fuckin' kill you hardcore, like everyone would come back injured in a ~thematic way~, but I took that out pretty quick. I snagged this spot right after Series 2 got opened before some asshole could try to put a Norman Conquest SCP there.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-11"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-11')">11</a>. Actual title, &quot;I ain’t never heard of no commy Fifthists or nothin'.&quot;
<p>This was just me writing an SCP based on that exact line from the <a href="/fifthist-hub">Fifthist Hub</a>. I don't think I executed it well but it's like at +60 which is real fuckin surprising. Roll that frog footage.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-12"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-12')">12</a>. i don't like humes or SRAs, and people usually don't use them consistently anyways, so why not write something about why that is? scranton is a woman this time because I Do What I Want. you can see this as an alternate universe—it's definitely not canon with SCP-3001 or SCP-3326—but i like to imagine that every other scp that's contained with reality anchors or that measures humes is Just Bullshit.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-13"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-13')">13</a>. This was my 4000-con entry; it came in 48th. The seed of the idea came from <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1379080&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437323" alt="Randomini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1379080)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;">Randomini</a></span>'s Cool War 2; I have no idea how this fits into the Cool War 2 canon, but I'm sure someone will make it work (the alien anartist is there as a plot hook). Irene's Daimon is inspired by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=617958&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437323" alt="Communism will win" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=617958)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;">Communism will win</a></span>'s 2000-con magnum opus, <a href="/scp-2020">&quot;Cliche, Right?&quot;</a>; can you figure out all the references?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-14"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-14')">14</a>. Overheard At Deer
<p>Sometimes you start talking shit in IRC and 7 hours later you've got a spicy new tale. ARD wrote most of the tweets, I did the handles and images. The sexy formatting is from TyGently's <a href="/intermission">Intermission</a>, which you should read because it's great.</p>
<p>Secret canon: Jean Cena is an scp-3331-1 instance. She's a trans lesbian and a Theatre/Ontokinetics major here to apply her natural Cena reality-bending abilities to the greatest performance art of them all, professional wrestling.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-15"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-15')">15</a>. Yep. This is accurate so far. Yes, even the chaos magick (sort of). Ask me about my magickal practice some time!</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-16"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-16')">16</a>. The seed of this idea was, as with everything I write now, a joke in the Third Law chatroom. This was originally supposed to be a collab between Taffeta and me but I wrote like 75% of it all in one go and there was nothing left to collab on. GreenWolf, Taffeta, TyGently, NineVolt and A Random Day all helped out with ideas and crit. And it's tagged as goi-format, not tale, because I have at least one more of these in the pipeline and consistency is key. Oh, and I don't actually play roller derby.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-17"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-17')">17</a>. Welcome to the Sports Zone, population me. I literally do not know anything about rugby, but that doesn't really matter, because the game itself rarely comes into play. This continues my quest to fill the Third Law canon with sports listicles until it hits a critical mass and i can spin off my own Sports Listicle Canon.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-18"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-18')">18</a>. SCP-2607 - Herpes ERPlex
<p>To quote the Wikipedia page on phone sex, &quot;A key advantage of phone sex, compared with physical intimacy, is that it cannot transmit a sexually transmitted infection.&quot;</p>
<p>The inspiration for this was a post on the OutOfContextSite19 tumblr, &quot;Terrible SCP idea: an STD that is somehow transmissible by reading erotica.&quot; If you were the person who said this in #Site19, this is your child. Congratulations.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-19"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-19')">19</a>. SCP-3337 - Death of the Artist
<p>I wrote this one after going to MoMa in New York while in the depths of a depressive episode. I was up on the top floor looking over a balcony and started having suicidal thoughts (the usual) and then i was like &quot;wait, what if i got one of those gallery labels and stuck it to the wall and THEN jumped&quot; and then i was like &quot;wait what if that was an SCP&quot;. At first it was just the tag, which summoned a jumper like once a day, but then i switched it, which i thought worked better.</p>
<p>it got a shoutout in the <a href="/lostandfoundation">LostAndFoundation</a> podcast which was pretty cool.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-20"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-20')">20</a>. This one is dedicated to my stepdad, who loves wine and hates reading instruction manuals.
<p>I honestly haven't decided whether these wine bottles actually come from Alagadda or that's the marketing angle MC&amp;D have decided to use. I might write a MCD-format article that explains that, either as the result of a (possibly millenia-long) trade agreement with one of the Masked Lords or as a clever marketing trick to spin some boring old blood rituals into something more exotic.</p>
<p>Originally this actually was going to be about a millenia-old relationship between MCD and Alagadda, but then Enzo appeared and I decided to cut all the ancient stuff about transport amphorae and ancient Roman religion. Thanks Enzo.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-21"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-21')">21</a>. JamCon2019 Theme 2: Pulp Fiction. I like the idea of using metafiction as a weapon, especially if there's not an easy way to get out of the fiction once you're in it.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-22"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-22')">22</a>. Honestly I gave this a 50/50 chance of being an instant classic or an instant deletion, and I'm glad the first option won. Be gay, do crimes, fuck capitalism. This was a not-quite-a-collab with <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kinchtheknifeblade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1345012); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1345012&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437323" alt="kinchtheknifeblade" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1345012)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kinchtheknifeblade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1345012); return false;">kinchtheknifeblade</a></span>.</div>
</div>

